jnxSvcFlowTableAggStatsTable.name: jnxSvcFlowTableAggStatsTable
jnxSvcFlowTableAggStatsTable.description: Aggregated statistics information about all flow tables on the service PIC interface.

jnxSvcFlowTableAggStatsEntry.name: jnxSvcFlowTableAggStatsEntry
jnxSvcFlowTableAggStatsEntry.description: An entry containing aggregated statistics for all flow tables for a particular service pic interface.

jnxSvcAggFlow.description: Total number of flows of any kind in the flow table.

jnxSvcAggFlowMaximum.name: jnxSvcAggFlowMaximum
jnxSvcAggFlowMaximum.description: Maximum number of flows of any kind in the flow table (high water mark).

jnxSvcAggFlowIdleFreed.name: jnxSvcAggFlowIdleFreed
jnxSvcAggFlowIdleFreed.description: Total number of flows of any kind that have been freed from the flow table by idle flow detection.

jnxSvcAggFlowTcpMaximum.description: Maximum number of TCP flows in the flow table (high water mark).

jnxSvcAggFlowTcpCreated.description: Total number of TCP flows that have been created in the flow table.

jnxSvcAggFlowTcpFreed.name: jnxSvcAggFlowTcpFreed

jnxSvcAggFlowTcpIdleFreed.name: jnxSvcAggFlowTcpIdleFreed
jnxSvcAggFlowTcpIdleFreed.description: Total number of TCP flows that have been freed from the flow table by idle flow detection.

jnxSvcAggFlowUdp.description: Total number of UDP flows in the flow table.

jnxSvcAggFlowUdpMaximum.name: jnxSvcAggFlowUdpMaximum
jnxSvcAggFlowUdpMaximum.description: Maximum number of TCP flows in the flow table (high water mark).

jnxSvcAggFlowUdpCreated.name: jnxSvcAggFlowUdpCreated
jnxSvcAggFlowUdpCreated.description: Total number of TCP flows that have been created in the flow table.

jnxSvcAggFlowUdpFreed.name: jnxSvcAggFlowUdpFreed
jnxSvcAggFlowUdpFreed.description: Total number of UDP flows that have been freed from the flow table for any reason.

jnxSvcAggFlowUdpIdleFreed.name: jnxSvcAggFlowUdpIdleFreed
jnxSvcAggFlowUdpIdleFreed.description: Total number of TCP flows that have been freed from the flow table by idle flow detection.

jnxSvcAggFlowPkt.name: jnxSvcAggFlowPkt
jnxSvcAggFlowPkt.description: Total number of packets processed by all flows.

jnxSvcAggFlowPktErr.name: jnxSvcAggFlowPktErr
jnxSvcAggFlowPktErr.description: Total number of packets found to be in invalid in processing by all flows.

jnxSvcAggFlowByte.name: jnxSvcAggFlowByte
jnxSvcAggFlowByte.description: Total number of bytes for packets processed by all flows.

jnxSvcAggFlowByteErr.name: jnxSvcAggFlowByteErr
jnxSvcAggFlowByteErr.description: Total number of bytes for packets found to be in invalid in processing by all flows.

jnxSvcAggFlowIcmpPkt.name: jnxSvcAggFlowIcmpPkt
jnxSvcAggFlowIcmpPkt.description: Total number of ICMP packets processed.

jnxSvcAggFlowIcmpPktErr.name: jnxSvcAggFlowIcmpPktErr
jnxSvcAggFlowIcmpPktErr.description: Total number of ICMP packets found to be in invalid for any reason.

jnxSvcAggFlowIcmpPktErrBadFlow.name: jnxSvcAggFlowIcmpPktErrBadFlow
jnxSvcAggFlowIcmpPktErrBadFlow.description: Total number of ICMP packets found to be in invalid because the flow was invalid.

jnxSvcAggFlowIcmpByte.name: jnxSvcAggFlowIcmpByte
jnxSvcAggFlowIcmpByte.description: Total number of bytes for all ICMP packets processed.

jnxSvcAggFlowIcmpByteErr.name: jnxSvcAggFlowIcmpByteErr
jnxSvcAggFlowIcmpByteErr.description: Total number of bytes for all ICMP packets found to be in invalid.

jnxSvcAggFlowTcpPkt.name: jnxSvcAggFlowTcpPkt
jnxSvcAggFlowTcpPkt.description: Total number of TCP packets processed.

jnxSvcAggFlowTcpPktErr.name: jnxSvcAggFlowTcpPktErr
jnxSvcAggFlowTcpPktErr.description: Total number of TCP packets found to be in invalid for any reason.

jnxSvcAggFlowTcpPktErrBadFlow.name: jnxSvcAggFlowTcpPktErrBadFlow
jnxSvcAggFlowTcpPktErrBadFlow.description: Total number of TCP packets found to be in invalid because the flow was invalid.

jnxSvcAggFlowTcpByte.name: jnxSvcAggFlowTcpByte
jnxSvcAggFlowTcpByte.description: Total number of bytes for all TCP packets processed.

jnxSvcAggFlowTcpByteErr.name: jnxSvcAggFlowTcpByteErr
jnxSvcAggFlowTcpByteErr.description: Total number of bytes for all TCP packets found to be in invalid

jnxSvcAggFlowUdpPkt.description: Total number of UDP packets processed.

jnxSvcAggFlowUdpPktErr.description: Total number of UDP packets found to be in invalid for any reason.

jnxSvcAggFlowUdpPktErrBadFlow.description: Total number of UDP packets found to be in invalid because the flow was invalid.

jnxSvcAggFlowUdpByte.description: Total number of bytes for all UDP packets processed.

jnxSvcAggFlowUdpByteErr.description: Total number of bytes for all TCP packets found to be in invalid.

jnxSvcServIdTable.name: jnxSvcServIdTable
jnxSvcServIdTable.description: Information about the service-identification service for the service PIC interface.

jnxSvcServIdTableEntry.name: jnxSvcServIdTableEntry
jnxSvcServIdTableEntry.description: An entry containing aggregate Service Identification service information applicable to particular service pic interfaces.

jnxSvcServIdPkt.name: jnxSvcServIdPkt
jnxSvcServIdPkt.description: Total count for all packets processed by service.

jnxSvcServIdByte.name: jnxSvcServIdByte
jnxSvcServIdByte.description: Total bytes for all packets processed by service.

jnxSvcServIdErrPkt.name: jnxSvcServIdErrPkt
jnxSvcServIdErrPkt.description: Total number of all packets found to be in invalid by this service during or as a result of processing.

jnxSvcServIdErrByte.name: jnxSvcServIdErrByte
jnxSvcServIdErrByte.description: Total butes for all packets found to be in invalid by this service during or as a result of processing.

jnxSvcServIdHeadExPkt.name: jnxSvcServIdHeadExPkt
jnxSvcServIdHeadExPkt.description: Packets processed by the service header examination function. This is the first packet for a flow for any service set specifying a header inspection rule set.

jnxSvcServIdHeadExByte.name: jnxSvcServIdHeadExByte
jnxSvcServIdHeadExByte.description: Bytes for all packets processed by the service header examination function. This is the first packet for a flow for any service set specifying a header inspection rule set.

jnxSvcServIdHeadExFlow.name: jnxSvcServIdHeadExFlow
jnxSvcServIdHeadExFlow.description: Packets processed by the service header examination function. This is the first packet for a flow for any service set specifying a header inspection rule set and only includes processing of packets that result in the creation of a flow.

jnxSvcServIdHeadExFlowMtch.name: jnxSvcServIdHeadExFlowMtch
jnxSvcServIdHeadExFlowMtch.description: Flows that matched any rule configured for the header examination function for the service set associated with the flow.

jnxSvcServIdHeadExProtoReq.name: jnxSvcServIdHeadExProtoReq
jnxSvcServIdHeadExProtoReq.description: Flows identified as requiring protocol inspection and URI extraction as a result of the header examination function.

jnxSvcServIdHeadExHttpProtoReq.name: jnxSvcServIdHeadExHttpProtoReq
jnxSvcServIdHeadExHttpProtoReq.description: Flows identified by header examination function as potentially requiring HTTP protocol inspection and URI extraction.

jnxSvcServIdHeadExWapProtoReq.name: jnxSvcServIdHeadExWapProtoReq
jnxSvcServIdHeadExWapProtoReq.description: Flows identified by header examination function as potentially requiring WAP protocol inspection and URI extraction.

jnxSvcServIdProtFlow.name: jnxSvcServIdProtFlow
jnxSvcServIdProtFlow.description: Flows currently undergoing protocol inspection and URI extraction. Does not include flows that have been marked as no longer requiring inspection or flows that are in an error state.

jnxSvcServIdProtInsPkt.name: jnxSvcServIdProtInsPkt
jnxSvcServIdProtInsPkt.description: Total number of packets processed by protocol inspection function while attempting to parse a transaction and extract URIs.

jnxSvcServIdProtInsByte.name: jnxSvcServIdProtInsByte
jnxSvcServIdProtInsByte.description: Total bytes for all packets processed by protocol inspection function while attempting to parse a transaction and extract URIs.

jnxSvcServIdProtInsFlowInsp.name: jnxSvcServIdProtInsFlowInsp
jnxSvcServIdProtInsFlowInsp.description: Total number of flows that have been inspected or are at present being inspected by the protocol inspection and identification function.

jnxSvcServIdProtInsFlowProtIdent.name: jnxSvcServIdProtInsFlowProtIdent
jnxSvcServIdProtInsFlowProtIdent.description: Flows for which the protocol inspection and identification function has determined the protocol in use and begun transaction processing.

jnxSvcServIdProtInsHttpUri.name: jnxSvcServIdProtInsHttpUri
jnxSvcServIdProtInsHttpUri.description: Number of HTTP transactions that have successfully extracted a URI.

jnxSvcServIdProtInsHttpUriMtch.name: jnxSvcServIdProtInsHttpUriMtch
jnxSvcServIdProtInsHttpUriMtch.description: Number of HTTP transaction URIs that were matched by a URI rule configured for the active service set.

jnxSvcServIdProtInsWapUri.name: jnxSvcServIdProtInsWapUri
jnxSvcServIdProtInsWapUri.description: Number of WAP transactions that have successfully extracted a URI.

jnxSvcServIdProtInsWapUriMtch.name: jnxSvcServIdProtInsWapUriMtch
jnxSvcServIdProtInsWapUriMtch.description: Number of WAP transaction URIs that were matched by a URI rule configured for the active service set.

jnxSvcServIdPktTcpMalform.name: jnxSvcServIdPktTcpMalform
jnxSvcServIdPktTcpMalform.description: Number of TCP packets found to be in invalid due to being malformed, for an incorrect sequence number, or other reason.

jnxSvcServIdWAPInvalidTxn.name: jnxSvcServIdWAPInvalidTxn
jnxSvcServIdWAPInvalidTxn.description: Numbee of packets found to be in invalid due to invalid WAP transaction identifier.

jnxSvcServIdErrWAPTxn.name: jnxSvcServIdErrWAPTxn
jnxSvcServIdErrWAPTxn.description: Number of packets found to be in invalid because the WAP transaction or flow was in an error state.

jnxSvcServIdErrHTTPTxn.name: jnxSvcServIdErrHTTPTxn
jnxSvcServIdErrHTTPTxn.description: Number of packets found to be in invalid because the HTTP transaction or flow was in an error state.

jnxSvcServIdHeadExFailCfgState.name: jnxSvcServIdHeadExFailCfgState
jnxSvcServIdHeadExFailCfgState.description: Number of header inspections that failed due to internal configuration state.

jnxSvcServIdProtInsFailCfgState.name: jnxSvcServIdProtInsFailCfgState
jnxSvcServIdProtInsFailCfgState.description: Number of URI inspections that failed due to internal configuration state.

jnxSvcTransactionWapCreated.name: jnxSvcTransactionWapCreated
jnxSvcTransactionWapCreated.description: Number of WAP transaction sessions created.

jnxSvcTransactionWapMaximum.name: jnxSvcTransactionWapMaximum
jnxSvcTransactionWapMaximum.description: Peak number of simultaneous of WAP transaction sessions since start.

jnxSvcTransactionWapFreed.name: jnxSvcTransactionWapFreed
jnxSvcTransactionWapFreed.description: Number of WAP transaction sessions freed.

jnxSvcTransactionWapIdleFreed.name: jnxSvcTransactionWapIdleFreed
jnxSvcTransactionWapIdleFreed.description: Number of WAP transaction sessions freed by idle clean-up.

jnxSvcTransactionHttpCreated.name: jnxSvcTransactionHttpCreated
jnxSvcTransactionHttpCreated.description: Number of HTTP transaction sessions created.

jnxSvcTransactionHttpMaximum.name: jnxSvcTransactionHttpMaximum
jnxSvcTransactionHttpMaximum.description: Peak number of simultaneous of HTTP transaction sessions since start.

jnxSvcTransactionHttpFreed.name: jnxSvcTransactionHttpFreed
jnxSvcTransactionHttpFreed.description: Number of WAP transaction sessions freed.

jnxSvcTransactionHttpIdleFreed.name: jnxSvcTransactionHttpIdleFreed
jnxSvcTransactionHttpIdleFreed.description: Number of WAP transaction sessions freed by idle clean-up.

jnxSvcServidProtInsUriErrProcess.name: jnxSvcServidProtInsUriErrProcess
jnxSvcServidProtInsUriErrProcess.description: Number of URIs that failed to process due to internal processing error.

jnxSvcServidProtInsUriErrTooLong.name: jnxSvcServidProtInsUriErrTooLong
jnxSvcServidProtInsUriErrTooLong.description: Number of URIs that were not processed because they exceeded the maximum supported URI length.

jnxSvcServidProtInsErrParseTx.name: jnxSvcServidProtInsErrParseTx
jnxSvcServidProtInsErrParseTx.description: Number of flows which experienced a transaction parse error or any kind that prevented URI extraction. This does not include length limitations or processing errors.

jnxSvcServidProtInsUriErrNoRes.name: jnxSvcServidProtInsUriErrNoRes
jnxSvcServidProtInsUriErrNoRes.description: Number of URIs that were not processed due to lack of system resources.

jnxSvcMIBCompliance.name: jnxSvcMIBCompliance
jnxSvcMIBCompliance.description: Compliance statement for the Juniper enterprise-specific service PIC interface service information MIB.

jnxSvcFlowTableAggStatsGroup.name: jnxSvcFlowTableAggStatsGroup
jnxSvcFlowTableAggStatsGroup.description: Basic aggregate statistics for flow table activity.

jnxSvcServIdiceGroup.description: Basic aggregate statistics for the Service Identification service.
